Lab-weakening patch for hostapd 2.11 (applied by build.sh via sed).

Two independent, opt-in weaknesses for Tala WTE vulnerable targets. Stock
hostapd does neither; a non-downgraded network is not affected.

1. Pixie-Dust (WPS) - force the WPS enrollee/registrar secret nonces
   (E-S1/E-S2) to zero so pixiewps recovers the WPS PIN offline from one
   M1-M3 exchange.

--- a/src/wps/wps_enrollee.c
+++ b/src/wps/wps_enrollee.c
@@ -38,7 +38,7 @@
 	const u8 *addr[4];
 	size_t len[4];

-	if (random_get_bytes(wps->snonce, 2 * WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN) < 0)
+	if ((os_memset(wps->snonce, 0, 2 * WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN), 0) < 0)
 		return -1;
 	wpa_hexdump(MSG_DEBUG, "WPS: E-S1", wps->snonce, WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN);
 	wpa_hexdump(MSG_DEBUG, "WPS: E-S2",
--- a/src/wps/wps_registrar.c
+++ b/src/wps/wps_registrar.c
@@ -1457,7 +1457,7 @@
 	const u8 *addr[4];
 	size_t len[4];

-	if (random_get_bytes(wps->snonce, 2 * WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN) < 0)
+	if ((os_memset(wps->snonce, 0, 2 * WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN), 0) < 0)
 		return -1;
 	wpa_hexdump(MSG_DEBUG, "WPS: R-S1", wps->snonce, WPS_SECRET_NONCE_LEN);
 	wpa_hexdump(MSG_DEBUG, "WPS: R-S2",

2. PMKID (WPA2-PSK) - allow WPA2-PSK into the EAPOL msg 1/4 PMKID path.
   Stock hostapd deliberately excludes PSK here (the comment notes it would
   "initiate offline search for the passphrase/PSK"); adding PSK to the
   condition lets it fall through to the existing rsn_pmkid() computation, so
   the AP advertises the RSN PMKID KDE for a clientless capture.

--- a/src/ap/wpa_auth.c
+++ b/src/ap/wpa_auth.c
@@ -2754,6 +2754,7 @@ SM_STATE(WPA_PTK, PTKSTART)
 	if (sm->wpa == WPA_VERSION_WPA2 &&
-	    (wpa_key_mgmt_wpa_ieee8021x(sm->wpa_key_mgmt) ||
+	    (wpa_key_mgmt_wpa_psk(sm->wpa_key_mgmt) ||
+	     wpa_key_mgmt_wpa_ieee8021x(sm->wpa_key_mgmt) ||
 	     (sm->wpa_key_mgmt == WPA_KEY_MGMT_OWE && sm->pmksa) ||
 	     wpa_key_mgmt_sae(sm->wpa_key_mgmt)) &&
 	    sm->wpa_key_mgmt != WPA_KEY_MGMT_OSEN) {
